name: dfs.namenode.read-lock-reporting-threshold-ms
description:
When a read lock is held on the namenode for a long time,
    this will be logged as the lock is released. This sets how long the
    lock must be held for logging to occur.

name: dfs.namenode.retrycache.expirytime.millis
description: The time for which retry cache entries are retained.

name: dfs.client.read.shortcircuit.buffer.size
description: Buffer size in bytes for short-circuit local reads.

name: dfs.client.deadnode.detection.probe.suspectnode.threads
description: The maximum number of threads to use for probing suspect node.
